description.en:
It is strongly recommended that every resource that should be rendered to an end user have at least one name.
Different types of name can be distinguished using classifications.
See: https://linked.art/model/base/#names

Arches note: This node's content should be the value for the title descriptor function, when used for a resource model.

* BranchId: la-name

Many resources have identifier values associated with them of different types, such as accession numbers, database numbers, lot numbers for auctions and so forth.  Identifiers are similar to Names, but instead use the Identifier class and do not have a language associated with them.
See: https://linked.art/model/base/#identifiers

* BranchId: la-identifier
